  "text": "Uniformly dispersed drug molecules in a nondegradable polymer matrix system (nanospheres) or for which the polymer degradation occurs after the drug release, have to dissolve and diffuse through the matrix to be released. The Higuchi equation (Equation 26) [CITATION_1] describes the diffusion-controlled release transport rate that is proportional to the square root of time:",
